2014-03-25 15:27:04	Lisa_Fox	gordonjcp, oh Alesis, love the design...
2014-03-25 15:27:05	<--	Pentapus_ (~Pentapus@nat-128-84-124-0-739.cit.cornell.edu) has quit (Ping timeout: 246 seconds)
2014-03-25 15:27:21	Lisa_Fox	gordonjcp, wavetable?
2014-03-25 15:27:41	gordonjcp	Lisa_Fox: it's got two large ROMs with samples in, and a firmware ROM with the start points
2014-03-25 15:27:48	Lisa_Fox	gordonjcp, I'm not sure if those are samples or FM instruments
2014-03-25 15:27:59	gordonjcp	the end points are encoded as magic values in the data
2014-03-25 15:28:06	Lisa_Fox	gordonjcp, Ah cool, love the sound from the demo you urled
2014-03-25 15:28:14	Lisa_Fox	ah i see
2014-03-25 15:28:17	Dianora	https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=740971779281171&id=178566888854999
2014-03-25 15:28:31	Dianora	Malaysian aircraft position analysis
2014-03-25 15:28:35	gordonjcp	Lisa_Fox: they do an interesting thing where the samples are 8 bit but the DACs are 16 bit
2014-03-25 15:28:36	Dianora	using doppler effects
2014-03-25 15:28:54	gordonjcp	Lisa_Fox: a marker byte signals the ASIC to "change gear" and shift the data down one bit
2014-03-25 15:28:55	Lisa_Fox	gordonjcp, oh neat! the S-50 is an oddball, i think it is 12bit
2014-03-25 15:29:06	gordonjcp	so you play back 8 bits worth of data on the upper 8 bits of the DAC
2014-03-25 15:29:20	gordonjcp	then hit the marker, and shift down to bits 14-7, and so on
2014-03-25 15:29:32	Lisa_Fox	gordonjcp, funky design scheme going on there. love the sound, and it sure looks cool as well.
2014-03-25 15:30:39	smrtz|nix	Hey, can someone help me figure out the antenna for a Bullet M5 please?  It's an N type connector, but it's much to heavy, and since I'll be building the antenna myself, I'm currious if I can just solder it directly to the bullet?
